# Step 11: Delete the EKS Cluster

### Why?

After completing the lab, delete the cluster to avoid AWS charges.

Delete the cluster

eksctl delete cluster 
--name mycluster 
--region us-east-2

This command automatically deletes:

* Amazon EKS Cluster
* Managed Node Groups
* EC2 Worker Nodes
* Auto Scaling Groups
* Launch Templates
* Security Groups
* VPC (created by eksctl)
* Public & Private Subnets
* Route Tables
* Internet Gateway
* CloudFormation Stacks

